---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="Leaves.PH · privacy and responsible use" pathname="/privacy">
  <article class="max-w-prose mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 pt-12 pb-16 text-ink-700 leading-[1.7]">
    <p class="kicker mb-4">SECTION 3 &middot; PRIVACY &amp; RESPONSIBLE USE</p>
    <h1 class="font-display font-medium tracking-tight text-ink-900 mb-3" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 3rem); line-height: 1.05;">Vegetation is not personal data.</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-500 mb-10 max-w-narrow">RA 10173 (Data Privacy Act of 2012), Section 3(g): "personal information" means any information from which the identity of an individual is apparent or can be reasonably and directly ascertained. Tree canopy aggregates per LGU do not meet that test.</p>

    <hr class="rule" />

    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink-900 mt-8 mb-3">What we publish</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-sm">
      <li><strong>Per-LGU aggregates only.</strong> 17 polygons. No per-building data, no per-household inference, no individual identification.</li>
      <li><strong>Source rasters cropped to NCR.</strong> Sentinel-2 RGB at 30 m, Hansen GFC v1.13, ESA WorldCover v200, Dynamic World v1, Meta canopy height v2 (reprojected to EPSG:4326). All public-record.</li>
      <li><strong>Per-LGU CSV.</strong> One row per (LGU, year). Columns: canopy_ha, canopy_pct, total_ha, hansen_loss_ha_cumulative, esa_tree_pct_2021.</li>
      <li><strong>Animation GIFs.</strong> 10 m to 30 m resolution time-series over hotspots (NCR-wide, SALEX corridor, Quirino Avenue, La Mesa watershed, per-LGU choropleth). No individual identification at these scales.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl text-ink-900 mt-8 mb-3">What we deliberately do not publish</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-sm">
      <li>Per-building canopy attribution.</li>
      <li>Backyard inventories.</li>
      <li>Photographs of identifiable people.</li>
      <li>Anything below 10 m granularity in any public artifact.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl text-ink-900 mt-8 mb-3">Public-record disclaimer</h2>
    <p class="text-sm mb-4">All inputs are public-record satellite imagery (Copernicus Sentinel data, NASA / UMD GLAD via Global Forest Watch, ESA WorldCover, Google Dynamic World, Meta AI canopy height) and public administrative boundaries (OpenStreetMap, Philippine Statistics Authority). Leaves.PH computes statistical indicators from these sources. Specific allegations of unpermitted tree cutting, if any, require independent investigation and corroboration. Patterns may have legitimate explanations.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl text-ink-900 mt-8 mb-3">Takedown channel</h2>
    <p class="text-sm mb-4">If you believe a published artifact identifies a specific private individual or violates RA 10173, file a private security advisory at <a href="https://github.com/xmpuspus/leaves-ph/security/advisories/new" class="no-underline text-accent-steel">github.com/xmpuspus/leaves-ph/security</a>. Acknowledged within 5 working days. Self-designated DPO: xpuspus@gmail.com.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl text-ink-900 mt-8 mb-3">Attribution required when redistributing data</h2>
    <p class="text-sm mb-4">Data products are CC-BY-4.0. When redistributing, cite as: "Leaves.PH (YYYY-Q-N), https://github.com/xmpuspus/leaves-ph". Upstream sources retain their own licenses, listed in the repo <a href="https://github.com/xmpuspus/leaves-ph/blob/main/LICENSE" class="no-underline text-accent-steel">LICENSE</a>.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl text-ink-900 mt-8 mb-3">Cookies and tracking</h2>
    <p class="text-sm">leaves.ph does not set any cookies. The site is statically served from Vercel; the only third-party request the browser makes is for OpenStreetMap base tiles (a.tile.openstreetmap.org / b / c). OSM logs your IP for tile serving; their privacy policy lives at <a href="https://wiki.osmfoundation.org/wiki/Privacy_Policy" class="no-underline text-accent-steel">osmfoundation.org/wiki/Privacy_Policy</a>. No backend, no auth, no analytics.</p>
  </article>
</Base>
